<paragraph id="8BDC3E199151777BFF4C7A8BDE52FF6E" blockId="51.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B917E20B9151777BFF4C7A8BDB5EFF05" box="[198,322,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
. A latinized form of the proper noun Solomon in reference to the 
<collectingCountry id="F3747E899151777BFBEC7A8BDF37FF06" box="[1126,1323,152,178]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
in which this genus is quite diverse. The genus name should be considered male in gender.
</paragraph>
