<paragraph id="8BDC3E199151777BFF4C7B03DF34FE16" blockId="51.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B917E20B9151777BFF4C7B03DB56FE9D" box="[198,330,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Comments.</emphasis>
Member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C63459A9151777BFDE07B03D8EFFE9D" authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[618,755,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Solomonius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917E20B9151777BFDE07B03D8EFFE9D" box="[618,755,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are relatively large for the 
<taxonomicName id="4C63459A9151777BFBC97B03DED7FE9D" authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[1091,1227,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Solomonius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917E20B9151777BFBC97B03DED7FE9D" box="[1091,1227,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. The male genitalia are distinctive in possessing elongate, robust, dorsolateral lobes. This is the only genus in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C63459A9151777BFF1D7B73DB3CFECD" authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,288,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Solomonius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917E20B9151777BFF1D7B73DB3CFECD" box="[151,288,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group in which the medial penile plates of the aedeagus are elongate and protrude outside of the genital capsule. Species in this genus can be distinguished from one another with the following key.
</paragraph>
